-- Sony seeks president, may succeed Stringer: report
-- 
-- Thu Nov 25, 2010 2:01am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/11/25/us-sony-stringer-idUSTRE6AO0YJ20101125

 

 TOKYO  (Reuters) - Sony Corp ( 6758.T ) ( 6758.T ) plans to look for a new president who could eventually succeed Chairman and Chief Executive Offier Howard Stringer, Bloomberg reported, citing people familiar with the matter. 

 Stringer, who took on the role of president in 2009 from Ryoji Chubachi, would retain the Chairman and CEO posts, Bloomberg said. (Reporting by  Nathan Layne ; Editing by  Edwina Gibbs )